<treatment ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6280905" ID-GBIF-Taxon="100059507" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6280905" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:CE017FC19EC7412EEDFAE9F69C89954B" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/CE017FC19EC7412EEDFAE9F69C89954B" lastPageNumber="135" pageNumber="135">
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="mainText">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis × pennatula">Acacia chiapensis x A. pennatula</taxonomicName>
. Shrub or small tree to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="m" value="5.0">5 m</quantity>
tall; twigs brown to dark reddish brown, puberulent. Enlarged stipular spines shiny, reddish brown, puberulent, usually terete in cross section, sometimes ridged or striate, broadly V-shaped with an angle of 160-180° (sometimes slightly reflexed), to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="70.0">70 mm</quantity>
long, 4.0- 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
wide near the base. Leaves 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="115.0" valueMax="160.0" valueMin="70.0">70-160 mm</quantity>
long; pinnae 14-30 pairs per leaf; rachis densely puberulent, rachis glands absent except between the terminal 1-3 pinna pairs; petioles grooved, densely puberulent, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4-8 mm</quantity>
long. Petiolar glands 1-3, nearly circular arid with a depressed apex, puberulent, striate, apex 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.9">0.9-1.5 mm</quantity>
across. Leaflets 28-36 pairs per pinna, lightly puberulent, linear, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="2.3499999999999996" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="1.9">1.9-2.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5-0.7 mm</quantity>
wide, one vein from the base, lateral veins not obvious, margins ciliate. Flowers and fruits not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
