<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="mainText">
Janzen (1974) observed that at two sites (below the dam at Temascal, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río" pageId="18" pageNumber="135">Rio</normalizedToken>
<misspelling corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@433d19e0" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">Chichicazapa</misspelling>
, and at Arroyo 
<misspelling corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@606de39c" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">Enmedio</misspelling>
, between Temascal, Oaxaca and La 
<misspelling corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@4e7a4839" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">Granja</misspelling>
, Veracruz, Mexico) 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis">Acacia chiapensis</taxonomicName>
may hybridize with non-ant-acacias such as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macracantha">A. macracantha</taxonomicName>
. At this site, numerous plants occurred that were 
<misspelling corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@3e1bbe6f" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">mtermediate</misspelling>
in spine, leaf, and branching morphology between these two species. During the present study no hybrids involving 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis">A. chiapensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macracantha">A. macracantha</taxonomicName>
were found; however, on a recent trip to Temascal (
<date pageId="18" pageNumber="135" value="1991-05">May 1991</date>
) the authors collected hybrid specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis × pennatula">A. chiapensis x A. pennatula</taxonomicName>
. Both parents were common in the pasture where the hybrid was collected and, except for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cornigera">A. cornigera</taxonomicName>
, were the only acacias in the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
